Excess requirements for applications for public procurement will be excluded by law
The legislation may establish exhaustive requirements for applications for participation in procurement.
In the autumn session at the plenary session of the state Duma plan to consider in the second reading the bill establishing the requirements for the content and composition of the application for participation in the purchase, the participants of which can be only small and medium-sized businesses.
Amendments are made by the government to the law "On procurement of goods, works, services by certain types of legal entities".
The draft law was developed in pursuance of the roadmap for the implementation of the Strategy for the Development of Small and Medium-Sized Enterprises in the Russian Federation until 2030, approved by the government.
It provides for the preparation of a draft law on an exhaustive list of documents that customers have the right to demand as part of the application from procurement participants - small and medium-sized businesses.
And also about the list of requirements for these documents.
To date, the law "On procurement of goods, works, services by certain types of legal entities" framework regulates the procurement activities of certain types of legal entities.
Requirements for the content, form, execution and composition of the application for participation in the purchase are set by customers independently in the procurement documentation.
“As a result, customers establish excessive requirements for the content, registration of the application, mandatory presence in its composition of certificates, certificates, extracts, the period of receipt of which in authorized bodies is comparable to the deadline for submitting applications, which leads to the inability to participate in such procurement and reduce the number of participants in the procurement,” the bill says.
The new bill provides for the establishment of an exhaustive list of documents that customers have the right to require in the application from procurement participants who are small and medium-sized businesses.
"The adoption of the document will eliminate the arbitrary establishment by customers of requirements for the composition and content of applications of participants who are small and medium-sized businesses," the explanatory note says.
