The authorities of the Moscow region told about the fate of closed landfills
In the suburbs continue to close landfills of solid household waste.
This year, the authorities promise to eliminate the latter.
Some of the 39 existing landfills in the region are being modernized into modern waste treatment complexes.
But this option is not possible for every landfill - many of them have grown dense residential development.
After the landfill is closed, it stands for reclamation - the body of the landfill is sprinkled with soils, degassing systems and infiltrate drainage are installed.
This allows you to stop the chemical processes inside the landfill so that it does not ignite, does not emit stench, does not poison the soil and groundwater.
And then the former landfill remains a useless heap among the surrounding residential buildings.
Why not make something useful out of it?
For example, in Ruz, where literally recently completed the reclamation of the landfill "Annino", the authorities are considering the option of making a heap of ski slope.
This landfill, which operated from 1976 to 2016, grew so that it went beyond the boundaries of the land allocated for it.
Therefore, during reclamation, it was necessary to buy out neighboring areas, de facto, already littered with garbage.
“Some time will pass, the training ground will “sit down”, the fortress will gain, and we will think what can be done so that it begins to bring benefits.
Directly in the eyes of the ski resort, "- said the head of the Ruza district Nikolai Parfenov.
Two landfills will become sites for the production of renewable energy sources
The landfills "Torbeyevo" in Lyubertsy and "Timokhovo" in the Bogorodsky district will become sites for the production of renewable energy sources from landfill and biological gases.
